[[image:Bee on flower.jpg|right|200px|Photo of bee]]
Old English [[beo|bēo]], from Germanic ''*bēō'', from Indo-European ''*bhī-''.  Cognate with Dutch [[bij]], dialectal German [[Beie]] ([[w:Upper German|Upper German]]), Swedish [[bi]]; and (''from Indo-European'') with Latvian [[bite]], Russian [[пчела]], Old Irish [[bech]].

